  Server-Side Event Tracking Documentation
  
  This implementation provides server-side event tracking using Shopify's analytics API
  and forwards events to GTM Server-Side when configured.
  
  SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
  
  1. Enable Server-Side Tracking:
     - Go to Theme Settings > Analytics & Tracking
     - Enable "Enable Server-Side Tracking"
  
  2. Configure GTM Server-Side (Optional):
     - Enter your GTM Server-Side URL (e.g., https://your-gtm-server-side-domain.com/collect)
     - Optionally enter your GTM Container ID for reference
     - Enable Debug Mode if you want to see events in the browser console
  
  3. Set Up Server-Side Proxy:
     You'll need to set up a server-side proxy that receives events from this client-side code
     and forwards them to your GTM Server-Side container. This can be done using:
     
     - Cloudflare Workers
     - AWS Lambda
     - Google Cloud Functions
     - A custom server endpoint
     
     The proxy should:
     1. Receive POST requests with JSON payload containing:
        - event_name: The name of the event
        - event_data: The event data object
        - page_context: Page context information
        - timestamp: Event timestamp
     
     2. Forward the event to your GTM Server-Side endpoint:
        POST https://your-gtm-server-side-domain.com/collect
        Headers: Content-Type: application/json
        Body: Transform the event data to match GTM Server-Side format
     
     Example Cloudflare Worker code:
     ```javascript
     export default {
       async fetch(request) {
         const event = await request.json();
         
         // Transform event to GTM Server-Side format
         const gtmEvent = {
           client_name: 'shopify-storefront',
           events: [{
             name: event.event_name,
             params: event.event_data
           }]
         };
         
         // Forward to GTM Server-Side
         const response = await fetch('https://your-gtm-server-side-domain.com/collect', {
           method: 'POST',
           headers: {
             'Content-Type': 'application/json'
           },
           body: JSON.stringify(gtmEvent)
         });
         
         return response;
       }
     }
     ```
  
  4. TRACKED EVENTS:
     - page_view: Triggered on every page load
     - product_view: Triggered when viewing a product page
     - add_to_cart: Triggered when adding a product to cart
     - remove_from_cart: Triggered when removing a product from cart
     - cart_view: Triggered when viewing the cart page
     - cart_updated: Triggered when cart is updated
     - begin_checkout: Triggered when clicking checkout buttons
  
  5. CUSTOM EVENTS:
     All events are also published to Shopify Analytics as custom events with prefix "plenty:"
     Example: "plenty:add_to_cart"
     
     You can subscribe to these events in Shopify Web Pixels or other analytics tools.
  
  6. PURCHASE TRACKING:
     Purchase events are typically tracked on the order confirmation page.
     You can add purchase tracking by:
     - Adding tracking code to the order status/thank you page template
     - Using Shopify's built-in checkout tracking
     - Creating a custom web pixel that subscribes to checkout completion events
  
  DEBUGGING:
  - Enable Debug Mode in Theme Settings to see events in the browser console
  - Check Network tab for requests to your GTM Server-Side URL
  - Verify Shopify Analytics custom events are being published (check browser console)
  
  NOTE:
  - All events use Shopify.analytics.publish() for Shopify Analytics integration
  - Server-side forwarding is optional and only works if GTM Server-Side URL is configured
  - Events are sent using navigator.sendBeacon() for better reliability during page navigation
{% endcomment %}
